'''Monte Porzio Catone''' is a ''[[comune]]'' (municipality) in the [[Province of Rome]] in the [[Italy|Italian]] region [[Latium]], located about 20 km southeast of [[Rome]], on the [[Alban Hills]]. As of [[31 December]] [[2004]], it had a population of 8,546 and an area of 9.4 km<U+00B2>.<ref name="istat">All demographics and other statistics: Italian statistical institute [[Istat]].</ref>

Monte Porzio Catone borders the following municipalities: [[Frascati]], [[Grottaferrata]], [[Monte Compatri]], [[Rome]].




==The Astronomical Observatory==
The Astronomical [[Rome Observatory]] is located 2 km out of city centre.
The Astronomic observatory is an important scientific structure,  has been projected in 1939 and finished in 1965, it rises above the rests of a Roman villa of the first century. The imposing construction rationalist, was used for preserving the equipments of the National Observatory in Rome, subsequently it became a structure to promote the astronomic and scientific popularization. Currently the observatory is endowed with the Astrolab and other didactic resources for initiatives to schools, university, associative and private groups.


==Hermitage Tusculan of Camaldoli==
Hermitage Tusculan Monastirian was founded in 1607 by [[Camaldolese]] Monks of Monte Corona. In 1613 the built was completed. The convent's church is devoted to Saint [[Romuald]]. The hospitality to pilgrims by the [[hermit]]s is guaranted and conditioned by rules as that in vigor, which prevents the entry in the hermitage to the women.
[[Image:Eremo_camaldoli.jpg|thumb|right|250px|[[Hermitage Tusculan of Camaldoli]].]]
